tre, Igboora, was kidnapped along side her daughter while returning from work on Monday evening. Although the kidnappers had on Tuesday evening through a phone call demanded a N4 million ransom for the duo to be released, it could not be confirmed whether a ransom was eventually paid. NAN reports that the incident was one of several being experienced in Ibarapa area of the state, particularly Igboora, with no fewer than 10 of such kidnap cases recorded in the last two years. Confirming the release of the victims, Gbenga Fadeyi, the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, said the duo were released unharmed. “I can confirm to you that the abducted wife of the monarch and her daughter have been released unhurt,” he said.(NAN) VANGUARD Olori Funbi Ojo, the wife of Oba Olusanjo Ojo, the Baba-Aso of Igboole in Igboora area of Oyo State, was on Monday evening kidnapped alongside her daughter by unknown gunmen. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the wife of the monarch is the Matron of Oyo State College… April 14, 2020 In "News" By Ola Ajayi, Ibadan After a lull in the activities of marauding kidnappers in the South-West zone, the wife and daughter of a king, Oba Olusanjo Ojo, Baba-Aso Of Igbole town of Igboora, in Ibarapa Central Local Government Area of Oyo State were reportedly kidnapped yesterday. The victims were said… April 14, 2020 In "News" **huge ransom paid **Monarch, police keep mum on ransom Dayo Johnson - Akure The abducted wife of a monarch in Ondo state, the Orunja of Odigbo, Olori Regina Akinrinmade, her two daughters and their driver yesterday regained their freedom. Olori Regina, her two daughters, Mercy and Precious and Lateef the… December 27, 2019 In "Metro"